id.title: Landing Page ID
id.description: A string that uniquely identifies this landing page.

name.title: Landing Page Name
name.description: The name of this landing page.

title.title: Landing Page title
title.description: The title of this landing page seen in the browser's title bar.

description.title: Landing Page description
description.description: The description of this landing page.

template_id.title: Landing Page template_id
template_id.description: The template_id of this landing page.

status.title: Landing Page status
status.description: The status of this landing page.

list_id.title: Landing Page list id
list_id.description: The list's ID associated with this landing page.

store_id.title: Store ID
store_id.description: The ID of the store associated with this landing page.

web_id.title: Landing Page Web ID
web_id.description: The ID used in the Mailchimp web application.

url.title: Published url
url.description: The url of the published landing page.

created_at.title: Created At
created_at.description: The time this landing page was created.

published_at.title: Published at
published_at.description: The time this landing page was published.

unpublished_at.title: Unpublished at
unpublished_at.description: The time this landing page was unpublished.

updated_at.title: Updated_at
updated_at.description: The time this landing page was updated at.

tracking.title: Tracking Settings
tracking.description: The tracking settings applied to this landing page.

track_with_mailchimp.title: Track with Mailchimp
track_with_mailchimp.description: Use cookies to track unique visitors and calculate overall conversion rate. Learn more [here](https://mailchimp.com/help/use-track-mailchimp/).

enable_restricted_data_processing.title: Enable restricted data processing
enable_restricted_data_processing.description: Google offers restricted data processing in connection with the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) to restrict how Google uses certain identifiers and other data processed in the provision of its services. You can learn more about Google's restricted data processing within Google Ads [here](https://privacy.google.com/businesses/rdp/).

_links.title: Links
_links.description: A list of link types and descriptions for the API schema documents.

items.title: Resource Link
items.description: This object represents a link from the resource where it is found to another resource or action that may be performed.

rel.title: Rel
rel.description: As with an HTML 'rel' attribute, this describes the type of link.

href.title: Href
href.description: This property contains a fully-qualified URL that can be called to retrieve the linked resource or perform the linked action.

method.title: Method
method.description: The HTTP method that should be used when accessing the URL defined in 'href'.

targetSchema.title: Target Schema
targetSchema.description: For GETs, this is a URL representing the schema that the response should conform to.

schema.title: Schema
schema.description: For HTTP methods that can receive bodies (POST and PUT), this is a URL representing the schema that the body should conform to.
